* Iron Raptor could feel Prowl shuffling around on her back, but since she 
was going a reasonable speed now she wasn't about to look back, risking 
stepping in a hole and breaking a leg.

But there was a threat of a new battle on the horizon and still a ship to 
repair, getting out of this beast mode was the first thing on her mind, then 
she would get down to work with the Maximals.
They...and she , were going to learn what the word TEAMWORK meant if it 
killed her.
And there was no room to deal with if anyone liked it or not.
This was a war for their future, not for their feelings.
And she was going to make sure that if a large battle did break out then the 
Maximals wouldn't be the ones left in the mud, they would stand and fight 
like the rest of the factions.

But without her robot mode she wasn't any use to anyone, and the sooner she 
found out what this was the better.


Iron Raptor sped up until she was at a full run, the surroundings seeming 
nothing more then a blur.
At this speed, they would make it to the Ark in no time.*
